#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:5
msgid "F2PY and Conda on Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:7
msgid ""
"As a convenience measure, we will additionally assume the existence of "
"``scoop``, which can be used to install tools without administrative access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:11
msgid ""
"Invoke-Expression (New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://"
"get.scoop.sh')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:15
msgid "Now we will setup a ``conda`` environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:17
msgid ""
"scoop install miniconda3\n"
"# For conda activate / deactivate in powershell\n"
"conda install -n root -c pscondaenvs pscondaenvs\n"
"Powershell -c Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope "
"CurrentUser\n"
"conda init powershell\n"
"# Open a new shell for the rest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:26
msgid ""
"``conda`` pulls packages from ``msys2``, however, the UX is sufficiently "
"different enough to warrant a separate discussion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/windows/conda.rst:30
msgid ""
"As of 30-01-2022, the `MSYS2 binaries`_ shipped with ``conda`` are "
"**outdated** and this approach is **not preferred**."
msgstr ""
